data.title: Darlington Borough Council Archives
data.text:
Symmetry Park

Overview Symmetry Park Darlington is in an excellent location, strategically positioned adjacent to the A66, to the east of Darlington Town Centre and accessed from Tornado Way. The site extends to 90 acres. 1,500,000sq ft has been constructed and let to Amazon. A second pre-let has been agreed for Unit 02 (138,250 sq ft). The […]

Darlington Science Park

Overview The town’s Science Park, centrally located next to Darlington railway station and the town, is home to some of the biggest developments in biosciences in the region. As one the UK’s leading independent technology innovation centres, CPI was selected to be the home of the National Biologics Manufacturing Centre, and the £38million centre is […]

Former Cleveland Bridge Site

Overview The former Cleveland Bridge site is a large manufacturing facility circa 400,000 sq ft on a 12ha site, with the ability to sub-divide. Located close to the A66, it has extensive hard standing and parking areas.

Greenbox Darlington

Overview In a prominent position next to the A66, Greenbox is home to 402,000sq ft of prime industrial, warehouse or logistics space with three units between 84,000 and 213,000sq ft on offer. These three units will be completed by the end of December 2024. For more information visit the website here or download the brochure […]

Morton Palms

Overview Morton Palms is a six hectare site with four hectares available for commercial development, with direct access to the A66. Investment is available freehold or leasehold.

Reflex Park

Overview Reflex Park is a new six hectare industrial/distribution location alongside the A66, with two industrial/distribution warehouses available. One is 77,769sq ft and the other 123,335sq ft.

Tornado Logistics Park

Overview Tornado Logistics Park is strategically positioned to access the Tees Valley and wider North East. Situated under a mile from the A66 and 5 miles to the both the A66 (M) A1 (M). These best in class, brand new units offer high quality warehouse space for the modern occupier. Initial proposal to provide 3x […]

Ingenium Parc

Overview Ingenium Parc is a development site situated on Salters Lane near Yarm Road. It is set to become Darlington’s premier location for industrial development in the borough. It is close to many established advanced manufacturing and engineering businesses, such as Cummins. It is a 41 hectare greenfield development site with excellent accessibility and adjacent to […]

Lingfield Point

Overview Originally built as the Patons and Baldwins wool factory, Lingfield Point’s award-winning space is home to some of the most significant businesses in the North East, including Wood Group, the Student Loans Company and Capita.
